title: Grateful Dead Live at Memorial Coliseum on 1977-05-17
description:
Set 1: Minglewood Blues, Mississippi Half-Step Uptown Toodeloo > El Paso, They Love Each Other, Jack Straw, Jack A Roe, Looks Like Rain, Tennessee Jed, Passenger, High Time, Big River, Sunrise, Scarlet Begonias > Fire On The Mountain

Set 2: Samson & Delilah, Bertha, Good Lovin', Brown Eyed Women, Estimated Prophet, Terrapin Station > Playing In The Band > Drums > Wharf Rat > Playing In The Band

E: Sugar Magnolia

reviews.review_text: Focus on Scarlet Plenty has been written about this show on the other versions of the tape, but I will add my two cents worth regarding Scarlet Begonias. It starts nice and energetic and not as slow and clunky as many of the preceding versions. In the guitar solo in the main head Jerry maybe plays one too many choruses, reaching for riffs that don't quite hit home. But this this general ambitiousness pays off in the jam, which is unusually playful and mines some different seams that a lot of other Scarlets. Its a standout version for me.
